import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['x'], bins=20, color='blue', alpha=0.7, edgecolor='black')
    plt.axvline(data['x'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['x'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('X-Coordinates')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of x-coordinates in the dataset?')
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    terrain_counts = data['name'].value_counts()
    terrain_counts.plot(kind='bar', color=['blue', 'green', 'red'])
    plt.xlabel('Terrain Type')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of terrain types in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(terrain_counts.index, title='Terrain Types')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
